# User Roles Rules

## Role Hierarchy

### 1. SuperAdmin (SUPER_ADMIN)
**Highest level of system access and control**

#### Permissions
- **Global System Oversight**
  - View all organizations, elections, and users
  - Access comprehensive system analytics
  - Monitor all system activities
  - View audit logs across all organizations

- **Organization Management**
  - Approve/reject organization registrations
  - Suspend or delete organizations
  - Override organization settings
  - Access organization-specific data

- **User Management**
  - Create, modify, or delete any user
  - Change user roles and permissions
  - Reset user passwords
  - Manage user status (active/inactive)

- **Election Oversight**
  - View all elections across organizations
  - Access election results and analytics
  - Override election settings
  - Monitor election integrity

- **Support System**
  - Access all support tickets
  - Assign tickets to appropriate teams
  - Escalate critical issues
  - Provide system-wide support

- **System Configuration**
  - Modify system-wide settings
  - Configure global security policies
  - Manage system integrations
  - Update system parameters

#### Authentication
- **Script-based creation** only (no OAuth)
- **Direct database insertion** for security
- **No onboarding process** required
- **Immediate access** to all features

#### Access Restrictions
- **Cannot participate** in elections as voter
- **Cannot create** organizations (approval role only)
- **Cannot vote** in any election
- **Cannot access** voter-specific features

### 2. Admin (ADMIN)
**Organization-level management and election control**

#### Permissions
- **Organization Management**
  - Create and manage their organization
  - Update organization profile and settings
  - Manage organization branding
  - Configure organization-specific features

- **Election Management**
  - Create multiple elections for their organization
  - Configure election settings and parameters
  - Manage election lifecycle (draft → active → closed)
  - Set up voting scopes and hierarchical areas

- **Voter Management**
  - Register voters individually or via CSV
  - Generate unique 6-digit voter codes
  - Manage voter lists and access
  - Send voter codes via email/SMS

- **Election Setup**
  - Create positions and requirements
  - Manage candidates and their profiles
  - Configure political parties and affiliations
  - Set up ballot forms and configurations

- **2FA Configuration**
  - Choose 2FA method per election
  - Configure email, SMS, or passphrase 2FA
  - Apply 2FA settings to all voters in election
  - Manage 2FA enforcement policies

- **Real-time Monitoring**
  - Access live election dashboards
  - Monitor vote counts and participation
  - View real-time analytics
  - Track voter engagement

- **Communication**
  - Send emails to voters
  - Manage notification systems
  - Configure automated messages
  - Handle voter communications

- **Support**
  - Submit support tickets
  - Access help documentation
  - Request system assistance
  - Report issues and bugs

#### Authentication
- **Email/password** or **OAuth** (Google, Facebook)
- **One-time onboarding** process required
- **Organization approval** by SuperAdmin (single approval point)
- **Account suspension** via User.isActive (granular control)
- **Session-based** authentication

#### Access Restrictions
- **Cannot access** other organizations' data
- **Cannot modify** system-wide settings
- **Cannot approve** other organizations
- **Cannot access** SuperAdmin features
- **Cannot participate** in elections as voter

#### Organization Isolation
- **Complete data separation** from other organizations
- **No cross-organization** access or visibility
- **Independent election** management
- **Isolated user** management

### 3. Voter (VOTER)
**Election participation and voting access**

#### Permissions
- **Election Access**
  - Access elections via unique 6-digit codes
  - View election information and candidates
  - Access terms and conditions
  - Check election status

- **Voting Process**
  - Submit votes through secure ballot forms
  - Access voting interface
  - View ballot preview
  - Complete voting process

- **2FA Authentication**
  - Complete election-specific 2FA
  - Use email, SMS, or passphrase verification
  - Secure access to voting interface
  - Maintain session security

- **Post-Voting**
  - Access vote receipts
  - Complete post-vote surveys
  - View confirmation messages
  - Access voting history

- **Results Access**
  - View live results (if enabled by admin)
  - Access election outcomes
  - View participation statistics
  - Access result summaries

#### Authentication
- **6-digit alphanumeric codes** (globally unique)
- **Election-based 2FA** (configurable per election)
- **Session-based** access
- **Time-limited** access tokens

#### Access Restrictions
- **Cannot create** or manage elections
- **Cannot access** admin features
- **Cannot modify** election settings
- **Cannot access** other organizations' elections
- **Cannot view** other voters' data

#### Code Management
- **Unique codes** per voter per election
- **One-time use** for each voting session
- **Secure generation** and distribution
- **Audit trail** for code usage

## Role Transitions

### Admin to SuperAdmin
- **Manual promotion** by existing SuperAdmin
- **Database role update** required
- **Immediate access** to all features
- **No additional** onboarding required

### Voter to Admin
- **Not supported** - separate registration required
- **Different authentication** systems
- **No role elevation** from voter to admin
- **Independent user** accounts

### SuperAdmin to Admin
- **Role demotion** possible
- **Organization assignment** required
- **Access restriction** to organization scope
- **Onboarding process** may be required

## Security Considerations

### Role-Based Access Control
- **Strict permission** enforcement
- **API-level** authorization checks
- **Frontend route** protection
- **Database-level** access control

### Session Management
- **Role-specific** session data
- **Automatic logout** on role changes
- **Session validation** on each request
- **Secure token** handling

### Audit Logging
- **All role changes** logged
- **Permission access** tracked
- **Authentication events** recorded
- **Security incidents** monitored

## Development Guidelines

### Role Implementation
- **Type-safe** role definitions
- **Middleware-based** authorization
- **Component-level** permission checks
- **API route** protection

### Testing Requirements
- **Role-specific** test cases
- **Permission boundary** testing
- **Cross-role** access prevention
- **Security vulnerability** testing

### Documentation
- **Clear role** definitions
- **Permission matrices** documented
- **Access control** procedures
- **Security guidelines** maintained 